Package: surveytidy
Title: Tidy dplyr/tidyr Verbs for Survey Design Objects
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Jacob", "Dennen", , "jacob.dennen@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides dplyr and tidyr verbs (filter, select, mutate, rename,
    group_by, arrange, slice_*, drop_na) for survey design objects created with
    the surveycore package. filter() uses domain estimation to preserve variance
    estimation validity; all other verbs preserve design variables and metadata
    automatically.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Depends:
    R (>= 4.3.0)
Imports:
    cli (>= 3.6.0),
    dplyr (>= 1.1.0),
    rlang (>= 1.1.0),
    S7 (>= 0.1.0),
    surveycore,
    tidyr (>= 1.3.0),
    tidyselect (>= 1.2.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    tibble
